<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Basic Intro</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Basic Introduction to HTML tags</h1>
  <h3><p>To start with HTML tags, we need to understand what is HTML? 
  <ul><li>HTML stands for Hyper-Text Markup Language.</li>
      <li>HTML is used to create webpages.</li>
      <li>With the use of html elements browser displays the content.</li>
      <li>The structure of web page is designed using HTML</li>
  </ul></p>
  <p> Few tags we commonly used are as follows :
  <ul>
    <li>The '!DOCTYPE html' declaration defines that this document is an HTML5 document.</li>
    <li>The 'html' element is the root element of an HTML page.</li>
    <li>The 'head' element contains meta information about the HTML page.</li>
    <li>The 'title' element specifies a title for the HTML page.</li>
    <li>The 'body' element defines the document's body, and is a container for all the visible contents.</li>
    <li>The 'p' element defines a paragraph</li>
    <li>The 'h1' to 'h6' tags defines the highest to lowest size of the content.</li>
  </ul></p></h3>
</body>
</html>
